static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5828843\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ita1705565048634.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ita1705565048634.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ita1705565048634.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ufn1665702550929\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To create libraries of modeled properties, global objects, and language setups, use the editors available in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span> menu.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__context_w3751ab1b5b1_w3752ab1b5_w3753ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__p_d12725e1_d12726e1_d12727e1\">To create a library for a global object:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__li_d5996e1_d5997e1_d5998e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__p_d12728e1_d12729e1_d12730e1\">In the Uniface IDE, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More\n                  Editors &gt;</span> and select the type of object you want to create. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">The Open Library dialog is displayed with a list of the available\n               libraries.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__li_d5999e1_d6000e1_d6001e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__p_d12731e1_d12732e1_d12733e1\">If you want to add a new library, click the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">+</span> button, and then enter a Library\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Name</span> and optional <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Alternatively, you can enter a non-existing name, in which case you will be\n                  prompted to confirm after clicking OK.</p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__p_d12734e1_d12735e1_d12736e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__fig_w3754ab1b5b3b3b3b3b1_w3755ab1b5b3b3b3b3_w3756ab1b5b3b3b3_w3757ab1b5b3b3_w3758ab1b5b3_w3759ab1b5_w3760ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Define Library Properties editor\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/createnewmsglib.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__note_w3761ab1b5b3b3b3b5_w3762ab1b5b3b3b3_w3763ab1b5b3b3_w3764ab1b5b3_w3765ab1b5_w3766ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> If the library is for use by all your Uniface applications, give it\n                  the name <code class=\"ph codeph\">SYSTEM_LIBRARY</code>. Otherwise, give it a name that is\n                  appropriate to its context.</div>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__note_w3767ab1b5b3b3b3b7_w3768ab1b5b3b3b3_w3769ab1b5b3b3_w3770ab1b5b3_w3771ab1b5_w3772ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Do not give it the name <code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS</code>, as this library\n                  already exists and is used by Uniface itself. When a new version or release of\n                  Uniface is installed, global objects in the USYS library may be deleted and\n                  replaced by new ones.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__li_d6002e1_d6003e1_d6004e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>, and if prompted to confirm, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Yes</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__li_d6005e1_d6006e1_d6007e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you are creating a library for Menus, Panels, Device tables, or Keyboard tables, create an item, then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> again.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ufn1665702550929__li_d6008e1_d6009e1_d6010e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The library or object editor is now opened so that you can add and edit objects in the library.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/loi1665702847852.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Global Objects</a><p>A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exe1665702665391.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$variation</a><p>Return or specify the name of the library containing objects needed by the application or component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fcq1665703251101.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$VARIATION</a><p>Specify the library name for global objects needed by the application when the application starts. Libraries are typed, so each global object library can have the same name which functions as a shared namespace which can be specified by this setting.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828843\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828843\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects To create libraries of modeled properties, global objects, and language setups, use the editors available in the More Editors menu. To create a library for a global object: In the Uniface IDE, choose More Editors > and select the type of object you want to create. The Open Library dialog is displayed with a list of the available libraries. If you want to add a new library, click the + button, and then enter a Library Name and optional Description . Alternatively, you can enter a non-existing name, in which case you will be prompted to confirm after clicking OK. Tip: If the library is for use by all your Uniface applications, give it the name SYSTEM_LIBRARY . Otherwise, give it a name that is appropriate to its context. CAUTION: Do not give it the name USYS , as this library already exists and is used by Uniface itself. When a new version or release of Uniface is installed, global objects in the USYS library may be deleted and replaced by new ones. Click OK , and if prompted to confirm, click Yes . If you are creating a library for Menus, Panels, Device tables, or Keyboard tables, create an item, then click OK again. The library or object editor is now opened so that you can add and edit objects in the library. Related Links Global Objects A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment. $variation Return or specify the name of the library containing objects needed by the application or component. $VARIATION Specify the library name for global objects needed by the application when the application starts. Libraries are typed, so each global object library can have the same name which functions as a shared namespace which can be specified by this setting. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}